```

---

# 🔬 Model Components

## 1. YOLOv8 Bacterial Detection

A custom-trained **YOLOv8** detector identifies bacteria belonging to four microbiological classes.

| Class ID | Label | Description |
|----------|-------|-------------|
| 0 | GPC | Gram-positive cocci |
| 1 | GNC | Gram-negative cocci |
| 2 | GPB | Gram-positive bacilli |
| 3 | GNB | Gram-negative bacilli |

### Outputs

For every image, YOLO generates:

- Bounding boxes
- Predicted class labels
- Per-class bacterial counts
- Class percentages
- Mean confidence scores
- Annotated visualization images

---

## 2. BLIP-2 Structured Caption Generation

The detected statistics are provided to **BLIP-2 (Flan-T5-XL)** using a carefully designed prompt that generates a standardized microbiology description.

The generated paragraph includes:

- Dominant bacterial class
- Morphology
- Gram reaction
- Expected stain color
- Secondary bacterial population (if present)
- Detection consistency
- Quantitative evidence

### Prompt Constraints

The language model is instructed to:

- Produce scientifically consistent descriptions
- Avoid hallucinated content
- Avoid diagnostic conclusions
- Generate a single cohesive paragraph
- Produce approximately 5–6 sentences
- Incorporate numerical detection statistics

---

## 3. Caption Evaluation

Generated captions are evaluated using two complementary methods.

### A. Rule-Based Microbiology Evaluation

The caption is automatically checked for:

- Gram reaction
- Morphology (cocci/bacilli)
- Stain-color description
- Numerical evidence
- Validation statement
- Sentence structure
- Absence of diagnosis
- Agreement with YOLO predictions

**Rule Score:** **0–100**

---

### B. CLIP-Based Semantic Evaluation

A CLIP vision-language model measures semantic similarity between:

- Gram-stain image
- Generated microbiology caption

This provides an additional quantitative assessment of caption-image consistency.

---

# 📂 Dataset

The detector is trained using the Gram-stain bacterial dataset available on Zenodo.

**Dataset**

https://zenodo.org/records/10526360

The detection dataset was converted from the original **640DataSet** into a YOLO-compatible detection format.

