# ⚙️ Installation

Clone the repository.

```bash
git clone https://github.com/yourusername/Automated-Gram-Stain-Interpretation.git

cd Automated-Gram-Stain-Interpretation
```

Install dependencies.

```bash
pip install ultralytics
pip install transformers
pip install accelerate
pip install bitsandbytes
pip install git+https://github.com/openai/CLIP.git
```

---

# ▶️ Usage

## Step 1 — YOLO Detection

Load the trained YOLO weights.

```python
model = YOLO("models/yolo_best.pt")
```

Run inference on the dataset.

The detector produces:

- Annotated images
- Detection statistics
- Confidence scores

---

## Step 2 — BLIP-2 Caption Generation

Configure:

- Dataset directory
- YOLO summary CSV
- BLIP model

Run the caption generation notebook.

Generated captions are saved in

```
reports/captions/
```

---

## Step 3 — Caption Evaluation

Execute the evaluation notebook.

The evaluation generates:

```
evaluation/
├── eval_results.csv
└── plots/
```

